This repository will contain the tools that will be coded for the peak calling benchmark project

// Programs:

eland2bed.cpp
	Convert the output of the eland aligner to bed format


// Scripts:
Note: All the scripts use DarkFishTechnology to manage cache, log commands and run
commands in parallel. (see https://github.com/sebhtml/NGS-Pipelines)

BenchmarkTools
	Collection of tools that are used in *_Analysis scripts

SISSR_Analysis.sh
	Usage:
	SISSR_Analysis.sh NumberOfProcessors FileFormat Options TreatmentFile ControlFile

	NumberOfProcessors: 	The number of processor the script is allowed to use.
	FileFormat: 		bed or eland.
	Options: 		The list of options in the same format as specified in SISSR
		 		documentation, between quotation marks. Minimally needs to 
				include genome size (i.e.: "-s 3200000000").
	TreatmentFile: 		The treatment file to analyze. Use relative path starting 
				from current working directory.
	BackGroundFile:		The background file to analyse. Use relative path starting
				from current working directory. Optional.
